http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: This is a foundation course for agriculture courses. Basic agriculture concepts are introduced, and students explore careers in the agriculture industry. Students will also be introduced to the FFA, leadership, and Supervised Agricultural Experiences.
Agriculture in Our Lives
Define terms
Identify ways in which agriculture affects us every day
List 100 agricultural products
Explain the importance of agriculture to the economy of the United States
Use a math problem to describe the importance of agriculture to the economy
Discuss ways agriculture has changed during the past 100 years
Identify careers in agriscience, production agriculture, agribusiness, agricultural mechanics, horticulture, forestry, and animal science
Invite speakers from each area to talk to the class about their profession
The National FFA Organization
Define terms
List the official FFA colors
Recite the FFA motto
Illustrate major events in the history of the FFA
Construct a timeline illustrating major events in the history of FFA using the Official FFA Manual Chronological History
Explain the purpose of SAEs
Animals in Agriculture
Define terms
List products obtained from animals
Match cuts of meat to the animals from which they are derived
Plants in Agriculture
Define terms
Discuss ways plants affect our lives
Take students on a tour of the campus to identify different types of plants
Label the four major parts of a plant, and discuss their functions
Identify requirements for plant growth
Natural Resources
Define terms
Explain why conservation of natural resources is important
Discuss strategies for conserving natural resources
Identify the major components of soil
Determine the texture of soil samples
Identify major species of wildlife in Arkansas
Use the Arkansas Game and Fish Regulations Guide as a reference
